					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Bullet Proof's Tetris uses the triangle at a pitch of $686 as a low fill or something, kinda unclear how it's supposed to work musically (though it's an appropriate bass note C, kinda). It wouldn't be caught by silencing $7FF though.<br /><br />In the high frequency case silencing the top notes is a compromise that produces a more accurate sound (despite less accurate underlying emulation) due to the limitations of your resampling process.<br /><br />In the low frequency case you're not getting more accurate emulation OR sound, so both of those goals are defeated. Maybe it sounds nicer though for games that do it. What games are these, btw? I haven't run into that problem yet.</div>

